###BEGIN_avg###
Usage: avg input index

Description:
	The avg function processes the input dataset by grouping its data based on the specified index and calculating the average of numerical columns within each group. The dataset must include unique non-numeric headers for each column.

Arguments:
	input_file	ex: test1.stat	Input file to be processed.
	index	ex: 1	Column for grouping.                    

Example:
	avg test1.stat 1	
##END_avg##


